Vintage-style illustration of a skilled craftsman at an old wooden workbench, carefully assembling an intricate mechanical lock mechanism made of gleaming brass gears and tumblers. The scene is lit by warm amber light from an antique desk lamp. On the workbench, multiple identical lock components are arranged in neat rows, suggesting mass production through a master template. In the background, faded blueprint papers with technical patterns are pinned to a cork board. The color palette features sepia tones, deep browns, and burnished gold, with subtle film grain texture throughout. The craftsman's hands are precise and deliberate, threading delicate metal pieces together like a puzzle. Small tools scattered nearby include tweezers, tiny screwdrivers, and a magnifying loupe on a brass stand.
